
<p>Summer for thee, grant I may be<br>
When Summer days are flown!<br>
Thy music still, when Whippowil<br>
And Oriole - are done!<br><br>
For thee to bloom, I'll skip the tomb<br>
And row my blossoms o'er!<br>
Pray gather me -<br>
   Anemone -<br>
Thy flower - forevermore!</p>

<p>Summer for thee, grant I may be<br>
When Summer days are flown!<br>
Thy music still, when Whipporwill<br>
And Oriole — are done!<br><br>
For thee to bloom, I'll skip the tomb<br>
And row my blossoms o'er!<br>
Pray gather me —<br>
Anemone —<br>
Thy flower — forevermore!</p>
